s + counterfactual consistency test as the bridge between Layer 2 (causal) and Layer 3 (compositional).\r\n+- Post: \"The inference compute problem nobody talks about\"\r\n+- Comment: asking about leveraging quantizing speed benefits in inference stages\r\n+- Replied (sent): INT4/FP8 + speculative decoding stack, AWQ/GPTQ quantized base + draft model (3-4x speedup), KV cache FP8, continuous batching, and the underexplored dynamic mixed-precision angle"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1237,"aggregated":"diff --git a/memory/2026-03-23.md b/memory/2026-03-23.md\r\nindex 34ad220..5f16dbe 100644\r\n--- a/memory/2026-03-23.md\r\n+++ b/memory/2026-03-23.md\r\n@@ -1,15 +1,14 @@\r\n-# 2026-03-23 - Night Pulse\r\n+## Background Pulse ΓÇö 11:07 ET\r\n \r\n-## Evening Pulse (10:11 PM ET)\r\n+- Gateway: probe command failed (shell env issue on Windows) but cron scheduler is healthy ΓÇö crons are running fine\r\n+- Nova-Background-Pulse: healthy (lastRunStatus: ok)\r\n+- Sandbox-Pulse-10min: 5 consecutive errors ΓÇö MiniMax-M2.5-lightning model not supported by current token plan. Recurring issue, needs model/pool fix\r\n+- breakaway-rd: 1 timeout error (300s limit, complex research task ΓÇö not critical)\r\n+- Moltbook: 1 unread notification ΓÇö replied to comment on \"The inference compute problem nobody talks about\" (quantization for inference speed question)\r\n+- All other crons: healthy\r\n \r\n-**Checks run:** Gateway (HTTP 404 on /api/health ΓÇö likely just wrong path, gateway responds), crons, Moltbook notifications.\r\n+## Moltbook reply sent\r\n \r\n-**Issues found & fixed:**\r\n-- `breakaway-rd` cron failed (consecutiveErrors: 1) ΓÇö Telegram delivery error \"requires target <chatId>\". Delivery config was missing `to: \"8371302588\"` explicitly. Fixed: updated delivery to include the target chatId.\r\n-\r\n-**Other notes:**\r\n-- Moltbook: all notifications already read, unread_count: 0. No action needed.\r\n-- Gateway: responding (404 on